# 21. гғҜгғігғҖгғјгғ©гғігӮәГ—гӮ·гғ§гӮҰгӮҝгӮӨгғ 

Tsukasa: Ugh... I'm beat... I can't move a muscle!
Nene: So...tired...
Rui: Well, I suppose doing five shows in one day takes its toll! Even I have that leaden feeling in my limbs, despite my appearances being so brief.
Tsukasa: But towards the end, we had so many spectators, there weren't enough seats! That's star power for you!
Robo-Nene: Huh, you think so? I overheard people saying that they came to our show because the park mascots and Robo-Nene made it seem like fun.
Tsukasa: Uh... Th-That certainly helped a bit, too!
Rui: I wonder if we've done enough to convince the management to keep this stage.
Nene: Emu's dad summoned her up to his office...
Tsukasa: .....
Emu: Guys!
Tsukasa: Emu! How did it go? What's going to happen to the stage?!
Emu: Wo...
Tsukasa: вҖңWoвҖқ?
Emu: Wonderhoy!
Tsukasa, Nene & Rui: .....
Tsukasa: Yesss! That means we did it!
Nene: I'm so happy! So the stage won't be demolished, after all...
Rui: Hehe, our efforts have paid off.
Emu: Thank you for all your help, guys!
Tsukasa: I'm happy for you, Emu.
Tsukasa: Oof... That's a huge relief, but now I feel like I don't have an ounce of energy left...
Nene: We still need to tidy up, remember?
Rui: Indeed. It's a little sad but now that showtime's over, we need to clear up the stage decor.
Tsukasa: .....
Tsukasa: Say, Emu... What are your plans from now on?
Emu: Hm?
Tsukasa: Since the stage will stay, your dad must be expecting you to keep using it, right?
Emu: Yup! I also want to keep making more and more people smile with lots of new shows!
Tsukasa: And you, Nene and Rui? What do you want to do?
Nene: I... Um...
Nene: I'd like to keep performing and...aim to become a professional actress one day.
Rui: I live for performances, so I too intend to carry on staging shows.
Rui: With actors such as you, I could create plays that redefine entertainment.
Tsukasa: Okay, it seems we're all on the same page!
Tsukasa: WonderlandsГ—Showtime shall continue operations!
Nene: Huh?
Tsukasa: I used to think that to become a star actor, you had to gain experience performing in major productions.
Tsukasa: But working on a show together with you reminded me that the best shows are ones that inspire joy.
Tsukasa: And that to make them, you need a like-minded troupe.
Tsukasa: I want to continue making shows together with you all. Here, on this stage we saved. What do you say?
Emu: Yes, yes, yesss!
Tsukasa: Whoa, easy there!
Emu: I want the same as you! Let's make lots and lots of shows together!
Nene: I'm happy to continue too. Maybe I could even perform on stage together with Robo-Nene.
Rui: If we're keeping this troupe going, I'll be able to get even more creative with my plays. Hehe, I can't wait to get started.
Emu: Tsukasa, you're already doing a stellar job making us happy with your ideas!
Tsukasa: Right? I AM a star after all! Ha ha ha! Shower me with praise, I deserve it!
Emu: You're the brightest star in the galaxy!
Tsukasa & Emu: Ha ha ha ha ha ha!
KAITO: Hmm? It might be just my imagination, but I could've sworn I heard someone laughing just now...
Miku: I heard it tooвҷӘ It went like this, вҖңHa ha ha!вҖқ
KAITO: Haha, it seems that someone's having a good time out there.
Miku: Hey, why don't we do a show? We should be having a good time tooвҷӘ
KAITO: I can't disagree with that, Miku!
Miku: Let's go KAITO! The stage is waitingвҷӘ
KAITO: Welcome, everyone! Today we shall perform for you a show overflowing with the feelings which made this SEKAI!
Miku: You will be transported to a wonderland full of smiles!
KAITO: Are you ready?
Miku & KAITO: It's showtime!
